column1: The download and use of Tradewebs MiFID II delayed transparency data available on this website (the "MiFID II Data") is subject to the following terms and conditions.

The MiFID II Data is available free of charge for your use in accordance with MiFID II and MiFIR, and ESMAs guidance set out in their document ESMA70 - 156 - 4263, "Final Guidelines on the MiFID II / MiFID obligations on market data".

In accordance with the referenced guidance, Tradeweb reserves the right to charge you for MiFID II Data in cases where you charge fees, whether directly or indirectly, for the redistribution of the MiFID II Data and/or for added-value services created from MiFID II Data.

Such fees on redistribution and added-value services include, without limitation: (i) a general fee for accessing your services; (ii) redistribution fees; (iii) a bundled fee; (iv) provision of unbundled research (v) terminal or portal fees including access to the MiFID II Data or derived data created from the MiFID II Data; and/or (vi) fees for any added-value services created, or derived from any or all of the MiFID II Data or such derived data created from the MiFID II Data.

Examples of added-value services/products include, without limitation: (i) trading algorithms; (ii) production of an index, benchmark, liquidity score or evaluated price; (iii) client facing services to encourage trading or order routing; (iv) transaction cost analysis; (v) predictive analytics and (vi) aggregating with other data sets or creating historical series.

If you are using the MiFID II Data for a purpose meeting one of the free use exclusions without an appropriate market data license from Tradeweb, such use will be liable to a fee in line with Tradewebs prevailing fee schedule for the period in which you are in breach of these terms and conditions.  If you would like to learn more about Tradewebs MiFID II market data products and/or arrange a market data license, please contact TWMiFMD@tradeweb.com for more information. Tradewebs MiFID II Market Data Fees disclosure is available here at https://www.tradeweb.com/disclosures/market-data-fees-disclosure/ .

The URL and access rights granted to you is for your personal use for the retrieval of the machine readable MiFID II Data that is licensed in accordance with the above terms and conditions.  Tradeweb reserves the right to revoke your access to the MiFID II Data if you are not (or Tradeweb has reasonable grounds to conclude that you are not) complying with these terms and conditions or are assisting third parties to avoid having to accept and agree these terms and conditions, and/or if you do not promptly respond to Tradewebs requests for information to verify your compliance with these terms and conditions.

The personal data that you provide in registering for access is used only for the purposes of managing your login account and Tradeweb may contact you regarding your usage of the MiFID II Data. By registering, you agree to the terms of the Tradeweb Privacy Policy. To learn more about how we use personal data and understand your rights, please review the Privacy Policy here at https://www.tradeweb.com/privacy-policy/ .

Tradeweb may revise and update these terms and conditions from time to time in our sole discretion. All changes are effective immediately when we post them and apply to all access to and use of the website thereafter. Your continued use of the website following the posting of revised terms and conditions means that you accept and agree to the changes. You are expected to check this page each time you access this website so you are aware of any changes, as they are binding on you.
